let, var, const

var
var is for variables available to the entire function 
var keyword is can be redeclared inside the same scope. brings up some serious issue. 
the new variable will replace the old one

let
let creates variables that are block-scoped
cannot be redeclared but can be updated

const - block scoped
Const variables cannot be updated or redeclared
Must be initialized

Scopes:
-Block 
Variables declared inside a { } block cannot be accessed from outside the block - let and const
Variables declared inside a { } block cannot be accessed from outside the block - var

-function
Variables defined inside a function are not accessible (visible) from outside the function.

-Global
All scripts and functions on a web page can access a global variable

Datatypes
When adding a number and a string, JavaScript will treat the number as a string.
